│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs inside                             │
│ BoUpSLP::getLastInstructionInBundle with the assertion E->getOpcode() ==      │
│ Instruction::PHI && \"Expected PHI\". This path is taken when BlocksSchedules │
│ contains an entry for the basic block (BB) and E->isGather() is false, but    │
│ getScheduleBundles(V) returns an empty array for the value V chosen to        │
│ identify the bundle. The code then asserts that the TreeEntry's opcode must   │
│ be PHI, assuming that only PHI nodes can reach this state.\n\n2. Analyzing    │
│ opt's Log:\n- The pass analyzes a store chain in bb2 and schedules the bundle │
│ of four stores.\n- It subsequently adds PHI bundles for the values being      │
│ stored.\n- During scheduling, it reports that the store bundle in bb2 is      │
│ ready and scheduled, and then attempts to check readiness on the defining     │
│ PHIs.\n- The crash happens when setInsertPointAfterBundle calls               │
│ getLastInstructionInBundle, and the internal logic attempts to look up        │
│ schedule bundles for V derived from E->Scalars. The 'Bundles' lookup returns  │
│ empty, and because BlocksSchedules.count(BB) && !E->isGather() is true, it    │
│ hits the assert expecting a PHI.\nThe debug log indicates that the pass is    │
│ actively working with a store TreeEntry in bb2, not a PHI entry, so the       │
│ assertion that only PHI opcodes reach this path is violated. This suggests    │
│ that there's a legitimate scenario where a non-PHI bundle may fail to find    │
│ schedule data, e.g., due to doesNotNeedToBeScheduled selecting a different V  │
│ or dry-run scheduling limitations.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe assertion  │
│ is too strict. The function assumes that when we have a BlocksSchedules entry │
│ for BB and the TreeEntry is non-gather, we must also have schedule bundle     │
│ data for the chosen V (or else the TreeEntry must be a PHI). However, in      │
│ practice, the schedule lookup may fail for non-PHI entries:\n-                │
│ doesNotNeedToBeScheduled(V) may select a value that wasn't included in        │
│ schedule bundles (e.g., constants, trivial ops), leading to                   │
│ getScheduleBundles(V) returning empty.\n- Early exits from buildTree_rec or   │
│ scheduling dry-run adjustments can leave some entries without schedule data   │
│ even if BlocksSchedules[BB] exists.\nWhen this happens, we should fall back   │
│ to the brute-force FindLastInst() logic, which is already provided later in   │
│ the function for cases where Res is null. Asserting on non-PHI opcodes here   │
│ causes a crash instead of gracefully falling back.\n\n4. Proposed Edit        │
│ Points(s):\n- Edit point: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp     │
│ lines 15110-15116.\nChange the behavior when Bundles is empty under           │
│ BlocksSchedules.count(BB) && !E->isGather(): instead of asserting that E is a │
│ PHI, fall back to FindLastInst(). This keeps the invariant of attempting to   │
│ find the last instruction via brute-force when schedule data is               │
│ missing.\nSpecifically, replace:\n  if (ArrayRef<ScheduleBundle *> Bundles =  │
│ BlocksSchedules[BB]->getScheduleBundles(V); !Bundles.empty()) {\n    ...\n    │
│ return *Res;\n  }\n  assert(E->getOpcode() == Instruction::PHI && \"Expected  │
│ PHI\");\nwith:\n  if (ArrayRef<ScheduleBundle *> Bundles =                    │
│ BlocksSchedules[BB]->getScheduleBundles(V); !Bundles.empty()) {\n    ...\n    │
│ return *Res;\n  }\n  // No bundles found for V despite having a block         │
│ schedule; fall back to brute-force.\n  Res = FindLastInst();\nThis preserves  │
│ the later assert(\"Failed to find last instruction in bundle\") after the     │
│ brute-force path, ensuring correctness.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe fix removes an │
│ overzealous assertion and adds a safe fallback to FindLastInst() when         │
│ schedule bundle lookup fails for a non-gather entry despite having block      │
│ schedule information. This addresses the crash by allowing the vectorizer to  │
│ compute the last instruction in the bundle without relying on schedule data   │
│ that might be missing for certain values, particularly in minimized or        │
│ edge-case IR like the provided reproducer. The expected effect is that the    │
│ SLP vectorizer completes without aborting, correctly setting the insertion    │
│ point and proceeding with vectorization."})                                   │
